Disappointing. A group of 8 of us went down to NO for my husband's 30th bday celebration. We stumbled upon this bar and we were pretty excited bec we love pubs and there was live music and a pool table. Half of our group ordered some beers and we sat down to listen to the music. My brother in law went up to the bartender and asked him if he could get two waters (one for my sister and one for me since I am 7 months pregnant and cannot and would not indulge in adult beverages). The bartender told him he would either have to buy two alcoholic beverages or pay for bottled water. My brother in law (who was sober) said that is f word ridiculous (the rest of my friends were sitting next to him and can verify this). I guess as I later learned from the bartender he thought my brother in law said f word off and immediately started yelling at my brother in law to leave the bar. My brother in law agreed and went over to tell me what was going on and asked me to let my sister know since she was using the bathroom at the time. Admittedly my brother in law used some choice words when telling me the story and told me he thought the bartender was an a word hole. Since my brother in law was trying to talk to me over the band and the bartender was doing his best to listen in, the bartender came over started yelling at him some more and my brother in law left the bar.  The abrasive bartender then came over to me and started telling me about his interaction with my brother in law. I said that not giving free tap water was strange to us bec we have never been in a bar that had a policy like that. If for no other reason then health/safety concerns. He said he needed to do it to pay for the band. I said if the bar ran a better business then they would not have to nickle and dime their customers. He kept at it and I finally told him that I thought it was ridiculous that a bar would not give a pregnant lady a free glass of water and I agreed with my brother in law. He then started yelling at me and told me that he was just giving me a "pass" earlier and I better leave the bar now. My husband jumped up (obviously alarmed that his pregnant wife was being yelled at) and asked him what his problem was and why he was being so dramatic over water. I grabbed my husband and the rest of our crew and we left since I saw no reason for the situation to become more heated.  There were literally three people in the bar when we entered and I am fairly certain I now know why. I have never been thrown out of a bar and did not expect my first time to be when I was 7 months pregnant asking for water. I am guessing if the bartender was more polite then the bar would have enough business to pay for their bands. I would avoid this place at all costs. It's another pretend dive bar that overcharges for drinks and has a pretentious/abrasive bartender.
